atholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8453669167318797e-19, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 455, \"end\": 461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\", \"score\": 0.9969549229651092, \"rank\": 0.0018089914431753907, \"text\": \"Gospel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A meme juxtaposing the contrasting styles of two Olympic marksmen is circulating the internet, and Catholics are giving it a shot.\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 602, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 571, \"end\": 580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3584302676593295e-24, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Catholics on X (formerly known as Twitter) have used the viral concept, which plays off the dramatically different approaches of two sharpshooters, to humorously take aim at distinctions between everything from the outlooks of priests and seminarians to the writing styles of different Gospel authors.\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 604, \"end\": 613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3584302676593295e-24, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 638, \"end\": 645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.756105414568314e-33, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}, {\"begin\": 890, \"end\": 896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\", \"score\": 0.9969549229651092, \"rank\": 0.0018089914431753907, \"text\": \"Gospel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The meme in question usually features South Korea rifle shooter Choe Dae-han, wearing specialized eyewear and contorting his body, on the left.\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 1050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.264444543870051e-14, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 971, \"end\": 975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_(Korean_surname)\", \"score\": 0.9999999938081601, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Choe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_(Korean_surname)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_(Korean_surname)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Immediately to the right is Yusuf Dike\\u00e7, the Turkish pistol shooter who has become an overnight sensation for his nonchalant, hand-in-his-pocket approach, which led to a silver medal win in Paris.\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1079, \"end\": 1090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yusuf_Dike\\u00e7\", \"score\": 0.9999978141955822, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yusuf Dike\\u00e7\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yusuf_Dike\\u00e7\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yusuf_Dike\\u00e7\"}, {\"begin\": 1096, \"end\": 1103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\", \"score\": 0.6749500335869802, \"rank\": 0.41256344472187007, \"text\": \"Turkish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1241, \"end\": 1246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Paris\", \"score\": 0.9998679513917935, \"rank\": 0.00013206604727533604, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Users then caption the respective competitors with contrasting people or ideas.\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Concepts are placed above Dae-han to indicate that they are relatively more complex or sophisticated, while users caption Dike\\u00e7 with an idea to express that it is relatively more simple and straightforward.\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1535, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The fact that Dike\\u00e7 medaled while Dae-han did not adds another wrinkle of meaning to the meme, usually suggesting, though not always, that whatever the Turkish pistol shooter is tagged with is relatively more effective or realistic, despite its no-frills approach.\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1689, \"end\": 1696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\", \"score\": 0.6749500335869802, \"rank\": 0.41256344472187007, \"text\": \"Turkish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In one bull's-eye use of the meme, Father Joseph Krupp, a priest of the Diocese of Lansing, Michigan,poked fun at the idealistic outlook of seminarians, drawing a comparison to the perspective of seasoned pastors.\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1845, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.021942345531244e-14, \"text\": \"Joseph\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\