, \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Errol_Flynn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Errol_Flynn\"}, {\"begin\": 3193, \"end\": 3210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_John_Paul_II\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1130035696898418e-47, \"text\": \"Pope John Paul II\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_John_Paul_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_John_Paul_II\"}, {\"begin\": 3271, \"end\": 3288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Benedict_XVI\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.82293077461576e-69, \"text\": \"Pope Benedict XVI\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Benedict_XVI\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Benedict_XVI\"}, {\"begin\": 3319, \"end\": 3325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9998812354132812, \"rank\": 0.00011836226647693678, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3436, \"end\": 3443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\", \"score\": 0.6749500335869802, \"rank\": 0.41256344472187007, \"text\": \"Turkish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Others used the meme todraw out the differencebetween Nouvelle Th\\u00e9ologie, a 20th-century theological movement known for its aesthetic style and emphasis on history, and Thomism, the theological approach associated with St. Thomas Aquinas and characterized by clarity and logical rigor.\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3509, \"end\": 3527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nouvelle_th\\u00e9ologie\", \"score\": 0.9999999683177526, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nouvelle Th\\u00e9ologie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nouvelle_th\\u00e9ologie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nouvelle_th\\u00e9ologie\"}, {\"begin\": 3678, \"end\": 3692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Aquinas\", \"score\": 0.9999979788738035, \"rank\": 2.0211300246192955e-06, \"text\": \"Thomas Aquinas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Aquinas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Aquinas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in another usage,St.\", \"from\": 3742, \"to\": 3766, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas was associated with the more \\\"complex\\\" side of the meme, his answer to the problem of evil contrasted with St. Augustine's.\", \"from\": 3767, \"to\": 3897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3767, \"end\": 3773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.617744861125006e-18, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even the so-called debate about \\\"integralism,\\\" a Catholic theory that holds that earthly governance must be directed toward man's supernatural end,was placed in the crosshairs: Jacques Maritain, the French philosopher who emphasized religious freedom, was juxtaposed with Charles De Koninck, a Belgian-Canadian Thomist who underscored the preeminence of the common good.\", \"from\": 3899, \"to\": 4269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3948, \"end\": 3956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8453669167318797e-19, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 4076, \"end\": 4092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Maritain\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jacques Maritain\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Maritain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Maritain\"}, {\"begin\": 4098, \"end\": 4104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999970335564629, \"rank\": 2.9664525557114842e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4171, \"end\": 4189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_De_Koninck\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charles De Koninck\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_De_Koninck\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_De_Koninck\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Outside of Catholic Twitter, the meme and variations of it have been used to contrasttypes of Greek columns,computer designers at different points in their careers, and even the way Poland and Ukraine are respectivelyresponding to Russian aggression.\", \"from\": 4271, \"to\": 4521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4282, \"end\": 4290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8453669167318797e-19, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 4365, \"end\": 4370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.9992720703584508, \"rank\": 0.0007254759489167583, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_l